text:
At least to me as a NixOS user, the real strength is that I have a single Git repo that defines every single piece of software and its configurations. My DNS for example:
```  services.nsd = {
    enable = true;
    # As anonymous as possible.
    identity = "";
    bind8Stats = true;
    # 3,600 (1h) = 60*60
    statistics = 3600;
    interfaces =
      [ "127.0.0.1" "::1" "148.251.123.12" "2a01:4f8:210:130b::4711" ];
    # Interactions with Hetzner DNS slaves:
    #
    #   <https://wiki.hetzner.de/index.php/DNS_Robot/en>
    zones = {
      "<http://stenetorp.se|stenetorp.se>" = {
        data = ''
          $ORIGIN <http://stenetorp.se|stenetorp.se>.
          $TTL 1h
          @ IN  SOA  <http://a.ns.stenetorp.se|a.ns.stenetorp.se>. <http://pontus.stenetorp.se|pontus.stenetorp.se>. (
            2019092702  ; serial
            1h          ; refresh
            17m         ; retry
            1w          ; expire
  …```
If it was all about binaries, pah, there is nothing wrong with other package managers when it comes to binaries.

